#	This file contains config info for /config/ra_flows object.
#	The format for the file is defined as:
#	The line starting with # defines comment
#	The first noncommented line is expected to be "version" number.

#	Every Flow information should start with the identifier 
#				RA_Flow:(The word is case sensitive).
# 	Following the flow identifier is the name of the flow and description 
#	of the flow and they should be in  the same line.

#	If the description contains more than one word with spaces 
#	they should be enclosed in doublequotes " ".
#	After Flowidentifier is the controlpoint name, object type and 
#	control pt descr and they should be in the same line.
#	The field delimiter in a line may be space or tab.
#	A sample format is given below
#	No Space or Tab is allowed between a single field 
#	other than description field
	

#	RA_Flow:  <Flow Name>  <Flow Description> 
# 	<Control_Point_Name 1> <Object Type> <Control Point Description> 
#	<Control_Point_Name 2> <Object Type> <Control Point Description> 
#	<Control_Point_Name 3> <Object Type> <Control Point Description> 

#	RA_Flow:  <Flow Name>  <Flow Description> 
#	<Control_Point_Name 4> <Object Type> <Control Point Description> 
#	<Control_Point_Name 5> <Object Type> <Control Point Description> 
#	<Control_Point_Name 6> <Object Type> <Control Point Description> 


